HEADWORD: Polynia
<hw>Po*lyn"i*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Russ.
<ets>poluineia</ets> a warm place in water, i. e., a place which does
not freeze.]</ety> <def>The open sea supposed to surround the north
pole.</def> <rj><au>Kane.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
